1
00:00:02,796 --> 00:00:03,964
Hyah!

2
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:37,102
[ Bird cawing ]

3
00:00:44,212 --> 00:00:45,913
[ Thunder rumbling ]

4
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:58,093
[ Laughing ]

5
00:00:58,161 --> 00:00:59,094
Oh, my lord.

6
00:00:59,162 --> 00:01:00,496
[ Laughs ]

7
00:01:00,563 --> 00:01:03,866
[ Indistinct conversation ]

8
00:01:19,016 --> 00:01:20,050
Let's go.

9
00:01:20,218 --> 00:01:23,254
Dear friend, join us in drink.

10
00:01:23,321 --> 00:01:24,155
Yes, brother.

11
00:01:24,222 --> 00:01:25,523
You've had a long journey.

12
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:26,590
You must be thirsty.

13
00:01:26,658 --> 00:01:29,660
This is no time for levity, Jason.

14
00:01:29,728 --> 00:01:31,162
Malachy, it's your father.

15
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:33,130
He's ill, and I think he may be dying.

16
00:01:33,198 --> 00:01:34,866
We need to leave.

17
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:36,167
[ Inhales sharply ]

18
00:01:36,235 --> 00:01:39,304
Unlike you, Jason, your brother
never had a problem with

19
00:01:39,372 --> 00:01:41,541
spoiling a perfectly good time.

20
00:01:41,608 --> 00:01:45,611
You tell me...
Why should I leave?

21
00:01:45,679 --> 00:01:49,248
He was the one who sent me away.

22
00:01:49,315 --> 00:01:53,719
Get up now, or you will know
what it feels like to be run through.

23
00:01:53,787 --> 00:01:56,689
Nobody told me I had to
bring you back alive.

24
00:01:56,757 --> 00:02:00,161
Join us and drink.

25
00:02:00,228 --> 00:02:01,496
Or meet the devil.

26
00:02:01,563 --> 00:02:08,669
You know, the last man who
told me that is in his grave.

27
00:02:08,736 --> 00:02:10,336
Jason.

28
00:02:15,377 --> 00:02:19,815
So you will not drink with us.

29
00:02:19,882 --> 00:02:24,186
[ Both grunting ]

30
00:02:24,254 --> 00:02:26,088
This is not the time, Malachy.

31
00:02:26,156 --> 00:02:27,554
You look well. Excuse me.

32
00:02:27,622 --> 00:02:31,657
[ Grunts ]

33
00:02:31,725 --> 00:02:32,892
Enough!

34
00:02:32,959 --> 00:02:35,595
It's been too long, Erik.

35
00:02:35,663 --> 00:02:38,364
[ Laughs ]

36
00:02:38,432 --> 00:02:41,166
Brother!

37
00:02:41,234 --> 00:02:44,435
Brother, do you honestly think
we've just been drinking and

38
00:02:44,503 --> 00:02:46,637
whoring our way around the continent?

39
00:02:46,705 --> 00:02:49,340
But of course we've done that.
Of course.

40
00:02:49,408 --> 00:02:51,876
We've also been practicing our skills.

41
00:02:51,944 --> 00:02:53,877
Every day. Every day.

42
00:02:53,945 --> 00:02:56,012
Well, almost every day.

43
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:59,149
Almost every day.

44
00:02:59,216 --> 00:03:01,384
[ Laughing ] Oh, you
are as good as ever.

45
00:03:22,202 --> 00:03:24,937
Now, are you ready to leave?

46
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:26,905
Now I guess I have no choice.

47
00:03:26,973 --> 00:03:28,006
[ Sighs ]

48
00:03:37,116 --> 00:03:38,584
Hyah!

49
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,954
Hyah! Hyah!

50
00:03:55,232 --> 00:03:56,765
Hyah!

51
00:04:03,669 --> 00:04:06,103
[ Thunder rumbling ]

52
00:04:14,944 --> 00:04:17,445
I cannot believe what has
happened to the kingdom.

53
00:04:17,512 --> 00:04:22,282
I've never seen anything
like this before.

54
00:04:22,350 --> 00:04:25,285
Come. We must hurry to
your father's side.

55
00:04:25,352 --> 00:04:26,352
Time is short.

56
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:27,620
Hyah!

57
00:04:44,835 --> 00:04:47,370
[ Sighs ] The gates are open.

58
00:04:47,438 --> 00:04:49,572
Not when I left.

59
00:05:54,026 --> 00:05:58,129
With this sword, I declare you
sovereign in place of your

60
00:05:58,196 --> 00:06:02,466
father, who died defending
his people and his kingdom.

61
00:06:02,534 --> 00:06:07,637
May you be worthy of this
ancient and holy symbol of rule

62
00:06:07,705 --> 00:06:11,306
and serve and honor your people.

63
00:06:11,373 --> 00:06:14,408
I should never have returned.

64
00:06:14,475 --> 00:06:17,743
These people need a leader.

65
00:06:17,811 --> 00:06:20,078
They need you.

66
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:25,183
[ Voice breaking ] I
have no bond with them.

67
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:29,690
You do.

68
00:06:29,757 --> 00:06:34,426
I am a warrior, not a politician.

69
00:06:34,494 --> 00:06:37,196
This is your birthright.

70
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:42,634
You are our king, Malachy.

71
00:06:42,702 --> 00:06:44,370
As it was meant to be.

72
00:07:03,054 --> 00:07:07,491
[ Bird cawing ]

73
00:07:07,559 --> 00:07:09,760
[ Sighs ] I've never seen
it like this before.

74
00:07:09,827 --> 00:07:12,728
Well, it stands to reason that
was the worst they ever had.

75
00:07:12,796 --> 00:07:14,029
Erik, this is pathetic.

76
00:07:14,097 --> 00:07:17,265
As I've already told you, it's
been like this for a long time.

77
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,267
It wasn't like this when I left.

78
00:07:19,335 --> 00:07:20,902
You were gone, Jason.

79
00:07:20,969 --> 00:07:22,269
How could you know?

80
00:07:22,337 --> 00:07:24,637
Come, now.

81
00:07:24,705 --> 00:07:27,472
We're here. We're together.

82
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:29,240
We can restore the kingdom.

83
00:07:29,308 --> 00:07:30,674
Your father tried.

84
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:33,842
- It took him years...
- Tried to what?

85
00:07:33,910 --> 00:07:37,412
To lose the respect of his people?

86
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,913
Look at them, Erik.

87
00:07:38,981 --> 00:07:40,615
They do not mourn him.

88
00:07:40,683 --> 00:07:41,850
Why would they?

89
00:07:41,917 --> 00:07:45,786
Your father died trying to
save Dragonoff, Malachy.

90
00:07:45,853 --> 00:07:47,920
Perhaps we should just
go back to the castle.

91
00:07:47,988 --> 00:07:49,788
Perhaps a king should know his people.

92
00:07:49,856 --> 00:07:52,324
With the greatest of respect,
sire, now might not be the

93
00:07:52,391 --> 00:07:55,826
safest time to do that.

94
00:07:55,894 --> 00:07:58,128
[ Scoffs ]

95
00:08:06,674 --> 00:08:07,741
[ Gasps ]

96
00:08:07,809 --> 00:08:08,909
It's okay.

97
00:08:08,976 --> 00:08:12,645
You need not fear me.

98
00:08:12,712 --> 00:08:15,247
Here. Take it.

99
00:08:15,314 --> 00:08:17,515
Meat! They've got food!

100
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:28,892
[ Insect buzzing ]

101
00:08:34,698 --> 00:08:37,332
We'll take it from them.

102
00:08:51,311 --> 00:08:52,979
You have food!

103
00:08:53,047 --> 00:08:54,180
Give it to us!

104
00:09:23,807 --> 00:09:26,575
You will hang for this, maggot!
Erik, no!

105
00:09:26,643 --> 00:09:29,044
They attacked us because
they are hungry.

106
00:09:29,112 --> 00:09:30,779
We cannot blame them for that!

107
00:09:30,847 --> 00:09:34,182
If you do not make an example out
of him, you will have anarchy!

108
00:09:34,249 --> 00:09:37,552
Go!
Guards! Chase!

109
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:43,523
You will have to trust my judgment.

110
00:09:43,591 --> 00:09:46,025
He's only been king for one day.

111
00:09:46,093 --> 00:09:47,626
Give him time, brother.

112
00:09:47,694 --> 00:09:50,629
[ Breathing heavily ]

113
00:09:50,697 --> 00:09:52,297
We must go.

114
00:09:58,936 --> 00:10:01,036
[ Thunder rumbling ]

115
00:10:09,779 --> 00:10:11,679
And I doubled the guard on the gate.

116
00:10:11,747 --> 00:10:14,281
No one will be able to walk in as we did.
Good.

117
00:10:14,349 --> 00:10:17,417
I've also placed 20 sentries
at various points around the perimeter.

118
00:10:17,485 --> 00:10:19,119
And I put locks on all of the doors.

119
00:10:19,187 --> 00:10:21,387
You did?

120
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:23,355
So why is that door open?

121
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:40,469
Apparently that wasn't
enough, brother.

122
00:10:40,537 --> 00:10:42,504
How did you get in here?

123
00:10:42,571 --> 00:10:46,407
I can see you're not
impressed by my magic trick.

124
00:10:46,475 --> 00:10:51,412
Perhaps something a
little more complicated.

125
00:11:23,107 --> 00:11:26,208
Unfortunately, the effects don't
last for long, and afterwards,

126
00:11:26,276 --> 00:11:29,345
the meat...Is terrible.

127
00:11:29,412 --> 00:11:31,947
What do you want with us, magician?

128
00:11:32,015 --> 00:11:34,015
My business is with the king.

129
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:38,385
I'm here to help him, and you,
defeat the scourge that killed

130
00:11:38,452 --> 00:11:41,287
his father and has all but
destroyed the kingdom.

131
00:11:41,354 --> 00:11:42,721
And you are?

132
00:11:42,789 --> 00:11:43,789
Kramer.

133
00:11:43,857 --> 00:11:45,291
Heinrich Kramer.

134
00:11:45,358 --> 00:11:47,827
And what is this scourge you speak of?

135
00:11:47,895 --> 00:11:49,795
Witches, gentlemen.

136
00:11:49,863 --> 00:11:51,864
This man is clearly mad, Jason.

137
00:11:51,931 --> 00:11:53,365
Throw him off the parapet.

138
00:11:53,432 --> 00:11:55,166
Let's see what he has to say.

139
00:11:55,234 --> 00:11:57,635
We could all do with a
bit of cheering up.

140
00:11:57,703 --> 00:11:59,903
Perhaps he has some more magic tricks.

141
00:11:59,971 --> 00:12:02,405
So you are suggesting the
failure of our crops is because

142
00:12:02,473 --> 00:12:03,473
of witchery?

143
00:12:03,540 --> 00:12:05,008
I do, sire, yes.

144
00:12:05,075 --> 00:12:06,876
Explain yourself.

145
00:12:06,944 --> 00:12:10,012
With pleasure.

146
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,081
What are these things?

147
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:14,116
That is a rapture stick.

148
00:12:14,184 --> 00:12:16,284
Rather, it is a piece of one.

149
00:12:16,352 --> 00:12:19,520
It is the prize of my collection.

150
00:12:19,588 --> 00:12:21,054
Careful with that.

151
00:12:21,122 --> 00:12:27,760
And this... this is the Belles
Finificus, my book of witches.

152
00:12:27,828 --> 00:12:30,895
I found it in the ruins of a village.

153
00:12:30,963 --> 00:12:40,236
Hundreds of people... men,
women, children... killed.

154
00:12:40,304 --> 00:12:42,805
Terrible.

155
00:12:42,873 --> 00:12:48,309
I've been trying to translate
it with some little success.

156
00:12:48,377 --> 00:12:51,112
These are the tools of my trade.

157
00:12:51,179 --> 00:12:53,914
And what trade might that be, sir?

158
00:12:53,981 --> 00:12:57,816
I am a witch hunter.

159
00:12:57,884 --> 00:13:02,519
I collect the signs of the dark forces
and record what I learn in my book.

160
00:13:02,587 --> 00:13:06,556
There is much evidence of the
witches I seek here in Dragonoff.

161
00:13:06,624 --> 00:13:09,558
And that fragment you hold in
your hand is one of the most

162
00:13:09,626 --> 00:13:12,461
powerful conveyors of the dark
forces that I have found.

163
00:13:12,529 --> 00:13:14,562
A witch's most-valued weapon.

164
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:18,599
With it, they can conjure the
blue fire of lightning, can

165
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:22,835
convey themselves as if on a
gust of wind, and, fortunately,

166
00:13:22,903 --> 00:13:25,738
few of the items in my
possession are of use to anyone

167
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:30,808
who has not invited the
dark forces into his soul.

168
00:13:30,876 --> 00:13:32,376
How convenient.

169
00:13:32,444 --> 00:13:37,714
So I understand correctly, you
are here to warn us of witches.

170
00:13:37,782 --> 00:13:42,951
And you wish for me to believe you?

171
00:13:43,019 --> 00:13:45,086
Without proof, sir, I cannot.

172
00:13:45,154 --> 00:13:48,156
Your father tried to silence me, too.

173
00:13:48,223 --> 00:13:50,724
His refusal to heed me killed him...

174
00:13:50,792 --> 00:13:53,760
As surely as if it had
been by his own hand.

175
00:13:53,828 --> 00:13:56,263
How dare you speak such treason!

176
00:13:56,331 --> 00:13:59,132
He was hiding something.

177
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:01,868
Why else would he keep you
ignorant of the state of the

178
00:14:01,936 --> 00:14:05,371
kingdom for so many years...
sending you off as a child,

179
00:14:05,439 --> 00:14:06,805
keeping you away.

180
00:14:06,873 --> 00:14:11,175
You are either a very brave
man or a very foolish one.

181
00:14:17,749 --> 00:14:23,452
There must be some...
Logical explanation for this blight.

182
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:26,688
Some strange manifestation of the plague.
Something.

183
00:14:26,756 --> 00:14:30,191
I find it incredibly hard to
believe that all of our troubles

184
00:14:30,259 --> 00:14:33,094
of the kingdom are because
of witches and spells.

185
00:14:33,162 --> 00:14:35,864
There is no drought.

186
00:14:35,931 --> 00:14:38,099
No disease.

187
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:42,568
Yet field after field is burned brown.

188
00:14:42,636 --> 00:14:48,773
That is because the witches
are devastating the crops.

189
00:14:48,841 --> 00:14:52,009
I can help you restore your kingdom.

190
00:14:52,077 --> 00:14:57,312
My father... he tried, and he failed.

191
00:14:57,380 --> 00:15:00,281
Are you implying that you could
succeed where he could not?

192
00:15:00,349 --> 00:15:03,016
I need your assistance in
battling the dark forces.

193
00:15:03,084 --> 00:15:07,352
I want you to go after the
witches and their queen with me.

194
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:10,922
I can teach you what I know,
but I cannot do it alone.

195
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:13,391
And why did you not enlist
the help of the villagers?

196
00:15:13,458 --> 00:15:16,193
They won't believe me.

197
00:15:16,261 --> 00:15:20,031
This is absurd.

198
00:15:20,099 --> 00:15:23,636
There are no such thing as
witches, merely an invention.

199
00:15:23,704 --> 00:15:27,973
Fairy tales told to naughty children.

200
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:30,408
There are no dark forces
coming to claim us.

201
00:15:30,476 --> 00:15:32,343
You are much like your father.

202
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:35,845
Don't make the same mistakes he made.

203
00:15:35,913 --> 00:15:37,980
Let me prove it to you.

204
00:15:38,048 --> 00:15:43,418
This day, have your pages call your
people to assemble in the town square.

205
00:15:43,486 --> 00:15:46,154
As entertaining as that
promises to be, I think not.

206
00:15:46,222 --> 00:15:50,592
Well, if nothing else, he could
bring the rabbits back to life.

207
00:15:50,659 --> 00:15:54,795
Let's give him a chance.

208
00:15:54,863 --> 00:16:00,400
Very well.

209
00:16:00,468 --> 00:16:03,236
You will have your chance.

210
00:16:15,348 --> 00:16:18,183
My brother and I are watching you.

211
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:22,053
You'll be mindful of that, lunatic.

212
00:16:22,121 --> 00:16:26,354
People of Dragonoff, I know
what causes the ills that have

213
00:16:26,422 --> 00:16:27,955
befallen the kingdom.

214
00:16:28,023 --> 00:16:31,959
It is witches who
move freely among us.

215
00:16:32,027 --> 00:16:36,730
This book has shown me how to
root them out and eradicate them.

216
00:16:36,797 --> 00:16:38,764
You must listen to me.

217
00:16:38,832 --> 00:16:40,933
The end of days is near.

218
00:16:41,001 --> 00:16:43,702
I have seen it with my own eyes.

219
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:48,971
It is witches that ruin the
crops and witches that threaten

220
00:16:49,038 --> 00:16:50,437
the village.

221
00:16:50,505 --> 00:16:54,874
They are among us even now.

222
00:16:54,941 --> 00:16:58,810
There is only one way
to end the starvation.

223
00:16:58,878 --> 00:17:02,947
We must burn the witches
... each and every one.

224
00:17:03,015 --> 00:17:06,250
Theirs is an evil... I
believe the lack of food

225
00:17:06,318 --> 00:17:08,752
makes your mind play tricks on you.

226
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:09,753
[ Laughs ]

227
00:17:09,821 --> 00:17:12,322
We will feed you and give you water.

228
00:17:12,389 --> 00:17:14,824
And you may continue on your journey.

229
00:17:14,892 --> 00:17:15,891
Make it happen.

230
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:21,063
One meal for one man will
not make a difference.

231
00:17:21,130 --> 00:17:23,465
My mind is sound.

232
00:17:23,532 --> 00:17:26,868
You cannot ignore what
you see around you.

233
00:17:26,935 --> 00:17:31,105
The kingdom and all its
inhabitants will perish unless

234
00:17:31,172 --> 00:17:32,639
you heed my words.

235
00:17:32,707 --> 00:17:38,111
You do not believe now, but I
will show you that mine are not

236
00:17:38,178 --> 00:17:41,780
simply the words of a starving madman.

237
00:17:47,385 --> 00:17:53,856
This powder, now the color of
oxblood, was once as bright as

238
00:17:53,923 --> 00:17:58,960
that which flows through your veins.

239
00:17:59,027 --> 00:18:04,597
It is of the witches themselves,
and will unmask the evil ones.

240
00:18:21,379 --> 00:18:25,982
Erik.

241
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:27,150
You must stop this!

242
00:18:27,217 --> 00:18:30,585
You! Stop this now!

243
00:18:30,653 --> 00:18:37,959
[ People screaming ]

244
00:18:38,027 --> 00:18:41,395
The powder has shown us our devil.

245
00:18:41,463 --> 00:18:43,264
It is she!

246
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:45,532
The dust says she's a witch.

247
00:18:45,599 --> 00:18:47,200
She must be burned.

248
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:48,434
Stop this!

249
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:50,269
What you've shown me is not proof.

250
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:52,972
It's nothing more than
misfortune carried by the wind.

251
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:56,309
Citizens, I have found
what ails your kingdom.

252
00:18:56,376 --> 00:18:58,043
You must burn this witch.

253
00:18:58,111 --> 00:18:59,744
Burn her!
Stop this!

254
00:18:59,812 --> 00:19:01,946
He's mad!
I beg of you, believe me!

255
00:19:02,013 --> 00:19:03,647
Believe me!
I am your king!

256
00:19:03,715 --> 00:19:04,748
You must stop this!

257
00:19:04,816 --> 00:19:09,718
Do what your dead king would not
and what your new king will not.

258
00:19:09,786 --> 00:19:11,953
Burn her! Burn her!

259
00:19:12,021 --> 00:19:13,355
Let us pass through!

260
00:19:13,422 --> 00:19:15,489
Make way for your king.

261
00:19:19,294 --> 00:19:23,527
Stop!

262
00:19:23,595 --> 00:19:24,662
Let her go!

263
00:19:24,729 --> 00:19:25,662
Let her go!

264
00:19:25,730 --> 00:19:27,364
Make way for your king!

265
00:19:31,603 --> 00:19:33,504
I beg of you, no!

266
00:19:33,571 --> 00:19:34,437
Let her be.

267
00:19:34,505 --> 00:19:36,138
Justice is being done.

268
00:19:36,206 --> 00:19:37,773
Why do you still doubt?

269
00:19:37,841 --> 00:19:38,740
You! You!

270
00:19:38,808 --> 00:19:40,108
This is your doing.

271
00:19:40,176 --> 00:19:43,044
You've taken the life
of an innocent woman.

272
00:19:43,112 --> 00:19:44,412
I had no choice.

273
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,580
This is only the beginning.
She is but one.

274
00:19:46,648 --> 00:19:47,914
There are countless others.

275
00:19:47,982 --> 00:19:50,049
You are your kingdom's only hope.

276
00:19:50,117 --> 00:19:51,917
You must act!
Hope? Hope?

277
00:19:51,985 --> 00:19:55,921
I cannot even stop my own people
taking the life of a guiltless grandmother.

278
00:19:55,988 --> 00:19:58,289
They care nothing of
hope and nothing of me.

279
00:19:58,356 --> 00:20:03,692
She's here.

280
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:07,328
At long last, it is time.

281
00:20:07,396 --> 00:20:11,465
Revel now, for time is short!

282
00:20:11,533 --> 00:20:17,669
The red queen...Is coming.

283
00:20:28,615 --> 00:20:31,649
[ Woman vocalizing ]

284
00:20:48,568 --> 00:20:51,004
[ Thunder rumbling ]

285
00:21:05,183 --> 00:21:07,384
It is blood!

286
00:21:07,451 --> 00:21:09,419
From the heavens!

287
00:21:14,858 --> 00:21:17,159
My God.

288
00:21:23,941 --> 00:21:26,309
I still don't believe this charlatan.

289
00:21:26,376 --> 00:21:28,510
You saw it with your own eyes.

290
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:30,746
The same as I did, Erik.

291
00:21:30,814 --> 00:21:34,982
There has to be some
plausible explanation.

292
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:37,450
And what might that be?

293
00:21:37,518 --> 00:21:40,920
Look, our only priority right
now is to defend the kingdom.

294
00:21:40,987 --> 00:21:44,822
We must prepare for anything,
plausible or otherwise.

295
00:21:44,890 --> 00:21:47,825
If this threat is real, and I
still don't believe it is, how

296
00:21:47,893 --> 00:21:50,461
are we to battle a coven of
witches with swords, bows,

297
00:21:50,529 --> 00:21:52,630
arrows, and potions?

298
00:21:52,698 --> 00:21:57,634
Mock my potions if you will, but my powder
did exactly as it was meant to.

299
00:21:57,701 --> 00:22:01,070
It saw beneath the benign
exterior to reveal the evil

300
00:22:01,137 --> 00:22:02,237
presence within.

301
00:22:02,304 --> 00:22:07,174
That's how they've infiltrated your
kingdom, sire... in the guise of innocence.

302
00:22:07,241 --> 00:22:08,975
Well, enlighten us, Heinrich.

303
00:22:09,043 --> 00:22:12,245
If they're so powerful, how do
you propose we defeat them?

304
00:22:12,313 --> 00:22:14,780
Well, my book has shown
me some secrets.

305
00:22:14,848 --> 00:22:16,148
Don't despair.

306
00:22:16,215 --> 00:22:17,448
[ Scoffs ]

307
00:22:17,516 --> 00:22:21,218
We cannot simply just stand here
and wait for the witches to attack.

308
00:22:21,285 --> 00:22:22,085
He's right.

309
00:22:22,153 --> 00:22:25,620
If what we saw today was any
indication, they have great power.

310
00:22:25,688 --> 00:22:28,424
We should ride at once and
take this enemy by surprise.

311
00:22:28,491 --> 00:22:30,458
It is our only hope of defeating them.

312
00:22:30,526 --> 00:22:34,628
I've seen witches
here, here, and here.

313
00:22:34,696 --> 00:22:38,097
Now, my book, I'm sure, shows
the location of their fortress.

314
00:22:38,165 --> 00:22:41,705
So far, the translation of that
part has eluded me, but there is

315
00:22:41,773 --> 00:22:45,143
this representation of a village.

316
00:22:45,211 --> 00:22:47,545
I believe we'll find it here,
at the very edge of our land.

317
00:22:47,613 --> 00:22:49,080
That's two days' ride from here.

318
00:22:49,147 --> 00:22:51,114
That's where we saw the
worst of the devastation.

319
00:22:51,182 --> 00:22:52,682
Very well.

320
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:57,285
We will leave immediately and
send word back when... if... we

321
00:22:57,353 --> 00:22:58,986
find witches.

322
00:22:59,054 --> 00:23:00,455
I am coming with you.

323
00:23:00,522 --> 00:23:02,591
Your kingdom needs its leader.

324
00:23:02,659 --> 00:23:04,227
Stay here where you're safe.

325
00:23:04,294 --> 00:23:07,262
The kingdom will be
defended by its king.

326
00:23:29,018 --> 00:23:33,489
Mile after mile of devastation.

327
00:23:33,557 --> 00:23:37,224
We have water, yet the crops fail.

328
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:41,425
The witches leech the plant's
energy to fuel their dark magic,

329
00:23:41,492 --> 00:23:45,528
like a vampire bat sucking
life from the land.

330
00:23:51,232 --> 00:23:54,865
What's that?

331
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:57,334
[ Shrieking ]

332
00:24:02,073 --> 00:24:03,239
Aaahh!

333
00:24:13,248 --> 00:24:16,350
Should there not be guardsmen
patrolling this area?

334
00:24:16,417 --> 00:24:17,918
Indeed there should be.

335
00:24:17,986 --> 00:24:21,889
By the gods, they'll pay with
their lives for leaving their posts.

336
00:24:21,956 --> 00:24:23,323
Calm yourself, brother.

337
00:24:23,391 --> 00:24:25,626
I'm sure there's a
perfectly good reason.

338
00:24:25,693 --> 00:24:27,694
Let's hope so.

339
00:24:27,762 --> 00:24:28,962
For their sake.

340
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:37,133
Go now.

341
00:24:37,201 --> 00:24:38,966
Get the witch hunter's book.

342
00:24:39,034 --> 00:24:41,768
Pry it from his dead
fingers if you must.

343
00:24:41,836 --> 00:24:43,769
Do not return without it.

344
00:24:55,546 --> 00:24:57,780
Aaaahhh!

345
00:25:03,723 --> 00:25:05,692
Still no sign of them.

346
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,327
It's quiet here.

347
00:25:07,395 --> 00:25:09,796
Yes, too quiet.

348
00:25:18,436 --> 00:25:20,370
Whoa.

349
00:25:24,045 --> 00:25:26,079
Make way!

350
00:25:30,384 --> 00:25:33,052
I said, "make way!"

351
00:25:47,033 --> 00:25:49,167
By the gods!

352
00:27:03,299 --> 00:27:04,666
I like this wench.

353
00:27:04,734 --> 00:27:05,766
She's spirited.

354
00:27:05,834 --> 00:27:08,268
Where are you and your friends from?

355
00:27:08,336 --> 00:27:08,969
Casi.

356
00:27:09,036 --> 00:27:10,668
Perhaps you've heard of it.

357
00:27:10,735 --> 00:27:12,934
We find the pickingsasier here.

358
00:27:13,002 --> 00:27:15,670
I should kill you right now.

359
00:27:15,737 --> 00:27:17,705
You fight well, madam.

360
00:27:17,772 --> 00:27:20,039
But you're clearly outmatched.

361
00:27:20,107 --> 00:27:22,474
I would suggest you reconsider.

362
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:25,877
Leader of murderers and thieves
who've killed two of our men.

363
00:27:25,944 --> 00:27:26,911
You were right.

364
00:27:26,979 --> 00:27:28,813
The blight has affected them, too.

365
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:29,747
They fight well.

366
00:27:29,815 --> 00:27:31,582
They would join us for a good cause.

367
00:27:31,649 --> 00:27:39,994
Besides, we could use a few good men.

368
00:27:40,062 --> 00:27:43,198
I am Malachy, your king.

369
00:27:52,409 --> 00:27:55,177
I offer you this choice.

370
00:27:55,244 --> 00:27:56,444
Join us.

371
00:27:56,511 --> 00:27:58,579
We fight witches.

372
00:27:58,647 --> 00:28:01,646
They intend to destroy the
kingdom and every one of us.

373
00:28:01,714 --> 00:28:05,182
Or die here on this day.

374
00:28:05,249 --> 00:28:07,282
Witches?

375
00:28:07,349 --> 00:28:09,150
What nonsense is this?

376
00:28:09,218 --> 00:28:10,818
You take me for a fool.

377
00:28:10,886 --> 00:28:17,222
We've seen their terrible
power with our own eyes.

378
00:28:17,290 --> 00:28:21,626
This fighting must end.

379
00:28:21,693 --> 00:28:24,328
We are not enemies.

380
00:28:24,395 --> 00:28:27,564
The threat is real.

381
00:28:27,631 --> 00:28:32,235
Join us and you will
live or die with honor.

382
00:28:32,302 --> 00:28:36,841
If you do not, I promise
you only a coward's end.

383
00:28:36,909 --> 00:28:39,043
Make your choice.

384
00:28:47,152 --> 00:28:48,951
We will join your quest.

385
00:28:49,018 --> 00:28:52,785
I'm honored by the opportunity
to serve my king.

386
00:29:59,770 --> 00:30:03,238
Ho!
What brings you so far from the castle?

387
00:30:03,306 --> 00:30:06,174
We expected to see you
earlier in our travels.

388
00:30:06,241 --> 00:30:07,942
But you were not at your post.

389
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:10,177
Two strange women approached us.

390
00:30:10,244 --> 00:30:14,180
They attacked us, tried to draw
the very breath from our bodies.

391
00:30:14,247 --> 00:30:16,081
They dragged us from the road.

392
00:30:16,149 --> 00:30:17,448
We had to kill them.

393
00:30:17,516 --> 00:30:19,651
Witches.

394
00:30:19,718 --> 00:30:23,120
They flew through the air
on a cloud of red mist.

395
00:30:23,188 --> 00:30:27,758
So they are dead, which means
we cannot question them.

396
00:30:27,825 --> 00:30:30,026
Yet you are still not
at your appointed post.

397
00:30:30,094 --> 00:30:33,062
While they pleaded for their
lives, they begged us to take

398
00:30:33,130 --> 00:30:36,264
them back to their village where
others of their kind would pay

399
00:30:36,332 --> 00:30:37,265
for their release.

400
00:30:37,333 --> 00:30:40,935
It's not far... just across the mountain,
about half a days' ride.

401
00:30:41,003 --> 00:30:42,203
We can take you there.

402
00:30:42,271 --> 00:30:44,905
Finally, you may be of some use to us.

403
00:30:44,973 --> 00:30:47,073
We camp here tonight.

404
00:30:51,711 --> 00:30:54,145
We must make a good plan of action.

405
00:30:54,213 --> 00:30:57,980
Learn as much as we can of this
... this witchcraft... if we

406
00:30:58,048 --> 00:31:01,250
wish to have any hope of
bringing an end to this.

407
00:31:01,317 --> 00:31:08,724
The book speaks of the hive-like
interconnection of their souls.

408
00:31:08,791 --> 00:31:14,832
So it stands to reason, we take down
their queen, the rest will follow.

409
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:18,002
Then we must strike at
her first and swiftly.

410
00:31:18,069 --> 00:31:21,338
What's this?

411
00:31:21,406 --> 00:31:24,207
A fierce weapon for such a timid man.

412
00:31:24,274 --> 00:31:28,409
I designed that crossbow with
a mechanism which rapidly

413
00:31:28,477 --> 00:31:29,910
reloads the arrows.

414
00:31:29,978 --> 00:31:31,778
It's fitted with a flame.

415
00:31:31,846 --> 00:31:35,848
The arrow tips are coated in
animal fat which ignite when

416
00:31:35,916 --> 00:31:37,582
they're ejected.

417
00:31:37,650 --> 00:31:42,252
Fire is one of the witch's
greatest weaknesses.

418
00:31:42,319 --> 00:31:45,320
This is good to know.

419
00:31:45,388 --> 00:31:47,255
And what is in that?

420
00:31:47,323 --> 00:31:49,289
Oh.

421
00:31:49,357 --> 00:31:55,860
This is the greatest secret of all.

422
00:31:55,928 --> 00:31:59,965
[ Chuckles ]

423
00:32:00,033 --> 00:32:01,601
Ahh.

424
00:32:01,669 --> 00:32:02,903
Delicious.

425
00:32:02,971 --> 00:32:06,241
Continue with your story.

426
00:32:06,308 --> 00:32:11,045
The village where everyone was killed?

427
00:32:11,112 --> 00:32:15,448
Before he breathed his last, the
village elder was able to tell

428
00:32:15,516 --> 00:32:19,619
me of a settlement of
devil-women and their leader,

429
00:32:19,686 --> 00:32:21,087
the red queen.

430
00:32:21,154 --> 00:32:24,856
Here is a passage about her.

431
00:32:24,923 --> 00:32:29,092
It speaks little of who she
is, but there is this.

432
00:32:37,766 --> 00:32:38,699
Erik.

433
00:32:46,641 --> 00:32:50,213
She certainly has the
beauty of a queen.

434
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:55,051
Beauty, perhaps.

435
00:32:55,119 --> 00:32:58,655
But from what I've been able to
translate, it seems she has no

436
00:32:58,723 --> 00:33:04,560
capacity to feel love
... only pure hatred.

437
00:33:04,628 --> 00:33:08,264
It could be the devil himself.

438
00:33:08,331 --> 00:33:10,599
Herself.

439
00:33:10,667 --> 00:33:15,036
Well, whatever it is, we need
to kill it before it kills us.

440
00:33:15,104 --> 00:33:20,541
"Death will come to the one who
rules the fiery coven only"

441
00:33:20,609 --> 00:33:27,512
if the essence she once shared
in love returns to her in full

442
00:33:27,580 --> 00:33:30,181
"with grace and sacrifice."

443
00:33:32,918 --> 00:33:36,953
A riddle.

444
00:33:37,021 --> 00:33:43,325
"But take heed, for her power
grows if she partakes but little

445
00:33:43,392 --> 00:33:45,193
of it."

446
00:34:30,166 --> 00:34:32,534
[ Gasping ]

447
00:34:35,304 --> 00:34:37,671
The queen will be pleased.

448
00:34:37,739 --> 00:34:45,809
How would you like to be a toad
in your precious forest, witch hunter?

449
00:34:50,646 --> 00:34:52,246
Aah!

450
00:34:55,750 --> 00:34:56,950
Witches.

451
00:35:02,589 --> 00:35:06,124
[ Breathing heavily ]

452
00:35:06,192 --> 00:35:09,060
Please, sire. Spare me.

453
00:35:09,128 --> 00:35:10,728
Don't listen to him.

454
00:35:10,796 --> 00:35:12,229
He's been possessed.

455
00:35:12,297 --> 00:35:14,098
He's not the man you knew.

456
00:35:14,165 --> 00:35:15,365
I'm no demon.

457
00:35:15,433 --> 00:35:20,303
From this moment on, we must trust
our instincts before our minds.

458
00:35:20,370 --> 00:35:22,037
Leave nothing to chance.

459
00:35:22,105 --> 00:35:25,407
Kill him.

460
00:35:25,475 --> 00:35:27,876
[ Grunts ]

461
00:35:49,817 --> 00:35:50,917
Jozefa?

462
00:35:50,985 --> 00:35:52,619
Yes, my queen?

463
00:35:52,687 --> 00:35:56,356
Do you bring me news of our sisters?

464
00:35:56,423 --> 00:35:59,860
Surely they have retrieved
the hunter's book by now.

465
00:35:59,928 --> 00:36:04,599
If they had, then they would be here
entrusting it to you, mother.

466
00:36:04,667 --> 00:36:07,469
Surely so, my dear.

467
00:36:07,537 --> 00:36:10,740
Unless they were dead.

468
00:36:10,808 --> 00:36:14,077
Perhaps the new king has killed them.

469
00:36:14,145 --> 00:36:17,882
Otherwise, they'd be safe within
the walls of this castle, and

470
00:36:17,949 --> 00:36:20,218
the book would be here with me now.

471
00:36:20,286 --> 00:36:23,322
I told you to retrieve the book.

472
00:36:23,390 --> 00:36:25,591
Didn't you understand?

473
00:36:25,659 --> 00:36:27,760
It must be destroyed.

474
00:36:27,828 --> 00:36:30,831
Yes, my queen.

475
00:36:30,899 --> 00:36:35,568
And the new king remain
unharmed in the doing of this

476
00:36:35,635 --> 00:36:37,635
simple deed.

477
00:36:41,873 --> 00:36:44,706
I see the resemblance.

478
00:36:44,774 --> 00:36:46,908
I do.

479
00:36:46,975 --> 00:36:51,344
Without it, I might not believe
you were my own blood.

480
00:36:51,411 --> 00:36:55,348
I saw what those men did to Baba.

481
00:36:55,415 --> 00:36:58,217
Barbarians.

482
00:36:58,285 --> 00:37:01,153
You couldn't have helped her.

483
00:37:01,220 --> 00:37:03,822
Could you?

484
00:37:03,890 --> 00:37:07,526
But you have something
for me, haven't you?

485
00:37:07,593 --> 00:37:09,728
Yes, m... [ Gags ]

486
00:37:23,502 --> 00:37:26,168
He's coming, isn't he?

487
00:37:26,236 --> 00:37:29,866
You're certain?

488
00:37:29,934 --> 00:37:32,601
Hmm.

489
00:37:32,669 --> 00:37:38,138
You abandoned our sisters
in the field, didn't you?

490
00:37:38,206 --> 00:37:40,773
You never abandon the coven, Jozefa.

491
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:43,141
Never.

492
00:37:43,209 --> 00:37:46,211
Speak to me. Speak.

493
00:37:46,278 --> 00:37:48,180
They possessed the
bodies of the soldiers.

494
00:37:48,247 --> 00:37:50,848
They did not need my assistance,
so I came to be by your side as

495
00:37:50,916 --> 00:37:52,082
you had commanded me, mother.

496
00:37:52,150 --> 00:37:55,918
What happened to them later
was not within my control.

497
00:37:55,986 --> 00:37:57,986
I see all.

498
00:37:58,054 --> 00:38:01,590
There is nothing that
remains hidden from me.

499
00:38:01,657 --> 00:38:02,457
Nothing!

500
00:38:02,525 --> 00:38:03,992
The coven fights as one.

501
00:38:04,059 --> 00:38:08,901
There is no one beyond our walls who
ouldn't burn a witch given half a chance.

502
00:38:08,968 --> 00:38:10,469
No sister shall stand alone.

503
00:38:10,536 --> 00:38:12,604
From this, we do not stray.

504
00:38:12,672 --> 00:38:15,741
We do not stray!

505
00:38:15,809 --> 00:38:19,545
No, mother, we do not stray.

506
00:38:19,612 --> 00:38:25,250
Their hosts have been killed, so their
essence is lost to the coven.

507
00:38:25,318 --> 00:38:26,184
So be it.

508
00:38:26,251 --> 00:38:27,385
Oh, leave me!

509
00:38:27,452 --> 00:38:30,289
I'll retrieve the book myself.

510
00:38:42,434 --> 00:38:44,901
[ Horse whinnies ]

511
00:38:56,278 --> 00:38:57,912
[ Growls ]

512
00:38:57,980 --> 00:38:59,213
Your highness!

513
00:39:06,287 --> 00:39:08,755
Kramer, is this another
of your tricks?

514
00:39:08,823 --> 00:39:09,989
Look at the eyes.

515
00:39:10,057 --> 00:39:13,193
It's the same unholy red as
the mist of the fiery coven.

516
00:39:13,261 --> 00:39:15,695
They are bewitched.

517
00:39:41,187 --> 00:39:42,554
Kramer!

518
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:52,793
With this, be still!

519
00:40:18,572 --> 00:40:20,005
Hurry. We must flee.

520
00:40:20,073 --> 00:40:23,106
The effects might not last for long.

521
00:40:36,916 --> 00:40:38,950
[ Sheep bleating ]

522
00:40:48,962 --> 00:40:51,797
I hear no church bells.

523
00:40:51,865 --> 00:40:56,633
And where's the steeple?

524
00:40:56,701 --> 00:40:58,302
This town is cursed.

525
00:40:58,369 --> 00:41:05,574
I've heard stories of travelers who have
come to trade and never return.

526
00:41:05,641 --> 00:41:07,842
The picture.

527
00:41:14,249 --> 00:41:16,551
Yes.

528
00:41:16,619 --> 00:41:19,188
The men have their instructions.

529
00:41:19,256 --> 00:41:20,390
They are ready.

530
00:41:20,458 --> 00:41:22,693
We must find the red queen at once.

531
00:41:22,761 --> 00:41:25,531
The book... Keep it safe.

532
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:29,339
The knowledge within it is
our only chance at victory.

533
00:41:29,407 --> 00:41:33,878
We'll be fighting magic
borne of the devil himself.

534
00:41:33,946 --> 00:41:35,947
We must fight for the people.

535
00:41:36,015 --> 00:41:37,750
For the kingdom.

536
00:41:37,817 --> 00:41:40,820
And for the memory of my father.

537
00:41:40,888 --> 00:41:47,527
And for those innocent ones who've
died at the hands of these demons.

538
00:41:47,595 --> 00:41:50,832
For those, too, madman.

539
00:42:17,919 --> 00:42:20,220
Greetings, gentlemen.

540
00:42:20,288 --> 00:42:21,288
Welcome.

541
00:42:21,355 --> 00:42:22,756
Greetings.

542
00:42:22,823 --> 00:42:24,657
It's a good morning for
trade, wouldn't you say?

543
00:42:24,725 --> 00:42:25,958
Indeed.

544
00:42:26,026 --> 00:42:30,189
I am Hobart, leader
of Cadistan village.

545
00:42:30,257 --> 00:42:34,725
It's very rare we see
strangers here in Cadistan.

546
00:42:34,793 --> 00:42:38,194
Your men, they seem weary.

547
00:42:38,262 --> 00:42:39,963
Indeed.

548
00:42:40,030 --> 00:42:42,732
Perhaps some refreshments
before market.

549
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:46,268
Your goods and horses will be
safe here until you return.

550
00:42:46,336 --> 00:42:47,469
That's very kind of you.

551
00:42:47,537 --> 00:42:48,036
Thank you.

552
00:42:48,104 --> 00:42:50,272
Please, follow me to
the meeting house.

553
00:42:50,339 --> 00:42:52,307
You can rest there.

554
00:42:52,374 --> 00:42:54,342
You must be hungry.

555
00:42:54,410 --> 00:42:55,510
Ale, my friend.

556
00:42:55,577 --> 00:42:56,710
That's what I need.

557
00:42:56,778 --> 00:42:58,212
Something's not right.

558
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,947
I'm gonna stay here, see
what I can find out.

559
00:43:01,015 --> 00:43:02,749
Good. We'll be inside.

560
00:43:02,816 --> 00:43:04,784
Look for the queen.

561
00:43:08,288 --> 00:43:10,789
Meat, gentlemen. Dine.

562
00:43:10,856 --> 00:43:12,290
Oh, you are a beauty, aren't you?

563
00:43:12,358 --> 00:43:13,891
[ Laughs ]

564
00:43:13,959 --> 00:43:15,193
Here, ladies.

565
00:43:15,261 --> 00:43:19,497
[ Indistinct conversations ]

566
00:43:19,565 --> 00:43:21,031
Here, right here.

567
00:43:21,099 --> 00:43:23,834
M-more food.

568
00:43:23,901 --> 00:43:26,970
Mmm. Mmm.

569
00:43:27,037 --> 00:43:28,371
[ Laughs ]

570
00:43:35,046 --> 00:43:37,046
Do you always dine so well?

571
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:39,016
And so early?

572
00:43:39,083 --> 00:43:41,684
[ Chuckles ]

573
00:43:41,752 --> 00:43:49,824
We have visitors so rarely...
It's cause for celebration!

574
00:43:49,892 --> 00:43:51,326
More ale!

575
00:43:51,394 --> 00:43:53,261
Yes, more ale!

576
00:44:15,009 --> 00:44:18,445
I'll best you every time, traveler.

577
00:44:18,513 --> 00:44:20,247
All right, then.

578
00:44:20,315 --> 00:44:22,987
Best of three.

579
00:44:27,054 --> 00:44:29,289
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

580
00:44:29,357 --> 00:44:30,924
This sport is childish.

581
00:44:30,992 --> 00:44:34,895
How about something more challenging?

582
00:44:34,962 --> 00:44:39,066
What do you have in mind?

583
00:44:39,134 --> 00:44:41,534
Your blades are certainly
sharp, my friend.

584
00:44:41,602 --> 00:44:43,734
Are you sure you know how to use them?

585
00:44:43,801 --> 00:44:46,870
The last man who said that
to me is in his grave, sir.

586
00:44:46,938 --> 00:44:47,704
[ Laughs ]

587
00:44:47,771 --> 00:44:49,038
What shall we wager?

588
00:44:49,106 --> 00:44:50,506
Nothing.

589
00:44:50,574 --> 00:44:54,009
This is for honor.

590
00:44:54,077 --> 00:44:56,578
For honor then.

591
00:44:56,646 --> 00:45:02,683
May the first strike win.

592
00:45:02,750 --> 00:45:04,817
Do you trust him?

593
00:45:04,885 --> 00:45:07,516
No.

594
00:45:07,584 --> 00:45:10,082
Have you noticed the numbers
increasing in the room?

595
00:45:10,117 --> 00:45:10,882
Yes, I have.

596
00:45:10,950 --> 00:45:14,385
Certainly doesn't seem like blight
and plague has affected this village.

597
00:45:14,453 --> 00:45:16,487
Hmm. Definitely not.

598
00:45:19,724 --> 00:45:21,758
We're wasting our time here.

599
00:45:21,826 --> 00:45:23,426
The madman was wrong.

600
00:45:23,493 --> 00:45:25,461
There are no witches here.

601
00:45:36,604 --> 00:45:38,238
Come now, gentlemen.

602
00:45:38,306 --> 00:45:40,106
This is a fight for honor.

603
00:45:40,174 --> 00:45:42,808
Do not leave before it is satisfied.

604
00:45:42,876 --> 00:45:44,510
We must go.

605
00:45:44,577 --> 00:45:46,478
No more fighting.

606
00:45:46,546 --> 00:45:48,781
I cannot let you leave, sir.

607
00:45:48,848 --> 00:45:53,251
Do not offend me, since I have
shown you so much hospitality.

608
00:45:53,319 --> 00:45:57,488
We appreciate your generosity.

609
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:03,527
Sire!

610
00:46:21,609 --> 00:46:25,243
A devil that is free.

611
00:46:35,519 --> 00:46:38,054
They are surrounding us.

612
00:46:45,526 --> 00:46:48,794
How easily men are lured.

613
00:46:48,862 --> 00:46:56,635
How easily they succumb
to flattery and ale.

614
00:46:56,703 --> 00:46:58,170
Why do you toy with us?

615
00:46:58,238 --> 00:46:59,204
Toy with you?

616
00:46:59,272 --> 00:47:01,773
You came here to slaughter me.

617
00:47:01,841 --> 00:47:03,642
You're after the blood
of the entire village.

618
00:47:03,710 --> 00:47:05,577
You and your kind have
devastated the crops,

619
00:47:05,645 --> 00:47:08,310
endangered my people, and you
intend to destroy my entire kingdom.

620
00:47:08,378 --> 00:47:09,444
What would you have me do?

621
00:47:09,512 --> 00:47:10,644
Your kingdom?

622
00:47:10,712 --> 00:47:14,612
Now that you have set me free,
I'm simply here to take back

623
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:16,280
what is rightfully mine.

624
00:47:16,348 --> 00:47:19,683
For decades I've been locked behind
the walls of this wretched village.

625
00:47:19,751 --> 00:47:22,519
We know what you are.

626
00:47:22,586 --> 00:47:25,822
And we will stop you.

627
00:47:25,889 --> 00:47:26,923
[ Scoffs ]

628
00:47:26,991 --> 00:47:31,862
Your pathetic army is no match for me,
even with your precious book.

629
00:47:31,930 --> 00:47:34,331
You should give it to me now.

630
00:47:34,399 --> 00:47:37,401
Save yourself a little bloodshed.

631
00:47:37,469 --> 00:47:38,802
Give it to me.

632
00:47:38,870 --> 00:47:42,472
You will have to kill me first.

633
00:47:42,540 --> 00:47:47,277
Where is it?

634
00:47:47,345 --> 00:47:49,179
Right here.

635
00:47:54,452 --> 00:47:55,685
How do we kill them?

636
00:47:55,753 --> 00:47:56,953
We don't. Let's go!

637
00:47:57,020 --> 00:47:58,521
Sire, it's time to leave.

638
00:47:58,589 --> 00:47:59,622
Damn it!

639
00:48:10,598 --> 00:48:13,132
They're surrounding us!

640
00:48:13,200 --> 00:48:14,800
Stay together.

641
00:48:43,489 --> 00:48:45,857
Kill them.

642
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:08,788
Come on!

643
00:49:19,099 --> 00:49:21,400
Behind you!

644
00:49:40,252 --> 00:49:41,719
Erik!

645
00:49:41,787 --> 00:49:44,321
Aaahhh!

646
00:49:52,395 --> 00:49:55,464
Erik!

647
00:49:55,531 --> 00:50:04,506
[ Weakly ] Jason... fight...
For the honor of our family...

648
00:50:04,574 --> 00:50:08,844
For our king.

649
00:50:08,912 --> 00:50:11,347
[ Exhales sharply ]

650
00:50:11,415 --> 00:50:15,483
I swear it!

651
00:50:41,805 --> 00:50:46,341
Aaaaaaah!

652
00:51:02,287 --> 00:51:03,820
My king...

653
00:51:12,633 --> 00:51:14,433
We must go.

654
00:51:14,501 --> 00:51:15,768
I cannot leave him.

655
00:51:15,836 --> 00:51:17,536
There's nothing you can do.

656
00:51:17,604 --> 00:51:19,972
You must save yourself
and your kingdom!

657
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:21,173
[ Breathing heavily ]

658
00:51:27,645 --> 00:51:29,346
Next time.

659
00:51:33,250 --> 00:51:35,017
[ Scoffs ]

660
00:51:35,085 --> 00:51:37,486
Take this one back.

661
00:51:37,553 --> 00:51:40,354
I'll deal with the rest later.

662
00:51:48,795 --> 00:51:52,030
The red queen is sure to pursue us.

663
00:51:52,098 --> 00:51:54,999
We have unleashed hell.

664
00:51:57,669 --> 00:51:59,535
Come on!

665
00:52:00,853 --> 00:52:04,088
[ Breathing heavily ]

666
00:52:04,156 --> 00:52:06,624
Good morning, pretty boy.

667
00:52:06,691 --> 00:52:09,460
My, you're quite a catch, aren't you?

668
00:52:09,528 --> 00:52:10,628
Go to hell.

669
00:52:10,696 --> 00:52:13,731
Oh, such language.

670
00:52:13,799 --> 00:52:18,736
I'm beginning to see why my
daughter is so taken with you.

671
00:52:18,803 --> 00:52:22,305
[ Grunting ]

672
00:52:22,373 --> 00:52:24,441
Oh, save your strength.

673
00:52:24,509 --> 00:52:26,844
I think I found a use for you.

674
00:52:26,912 --> 00:52:29,982
I'll tell you nothing, hag.

675
00:52:30,049 --> 00:52:32,285
Torture me all you wish.

676
00:52:32,353 --> 00:52:34,154
Torture?

677
00:52:34,222 --> 00:52:39,126
Hmm. Indeed.

678
00:52:39,194 --> 00:52:40,728
Aaaaah!

679
00:52:40,796 --> 00:52:43,098
Aaaah!

680
00:52:43,165 --> 00:52:45,534
[ Gasping ]

681
00:52:45,601 --> 00:52:50,205
[ Grunting ]

682
00:52:50,273 --> 00:52:57,743
I hope you're ready to
see your kingdom bleed.

683
00:52:57,811 --> 00:52:59,544
[ Scoffs ]

684
00:52:59,611 --> 00:53:01,612
[ Moans ]

685
00:53:22,993 --> 00:53:25,328
Sire, you must talk to your people.

686
00:53:25,395 --> 00:53:27,163
Let them know what's happening.

687
00:53:27,230 --> 00:53:28,063
Prepare them.

688
00:53:28,131 --> 00:53:30,433
They'll listen to you now.

689
00:53:30,501 --> 00:53:33,002
Let them see your compassion.

690
00:53:33,070 --> 00:53:35,504
People of the kingdom! Come!

691
00:53:35,572 --> 00:53:41,643
Listen to your king!

692
00:53:41,711 --> 00:53:45,647
I must warn you of the coming danger
that threatens every one of us.

693
00:53:45,714 --> 00:53:50,618
What you have all been through,
no people should suffer.

694
00:53:50,686 --> 00:53:54,821
I see your hunger, and I
understand your fear.

695
00:53:54,888 --> 00:53:58,623
But we cannot, we must
not succumb to it.

696
00:53:58,691 --> 00:54:03,793
What we have all seen, the death
of our comrades, our friends, it

697
00:54:03,860 --> 00:54:06,561
was not the work of plague or blight.

698
00:54:06,629 --> 00:54:10,731
This was the work of witches, witches
with whom we have fought already.

699
00:54:10,799 --> 00:54:12,866
Witches with whom we have battled.

700
00:54:12,934 --> 00:54:16,470
What happens to this
kingdom happens to you.

701
00:54:16,538 --> 00:54:18,672
But it happens to me, also.

702
00:54:18,740 --> 00:54:24,177
Because it is in my heart, my
blood, and in my soul, and for

703
00:54:24,245 --> 00:54:28,949
that, I ask you, my people, to
help me fight this evil... this

704
00:54:29,017 --> 00:54:32,419
unholy evil... that comes to
threaten every one of us.

705
00:54:32,487 --> 00:54:33,986
How can we fight them?

706
00:54:34,054 --> 00:54:35,020
We're too weak.

707
00:54:35,087 --> 00:54:37,856
And what will you tell
your children, sir?

708
00:54:37,923 --> 00:54:42,059
That they should die a
convenient death of starvation

709
00:54:42,127 --> 00:54:44,662
while they sleep in their beds
at night, or they should stand

710
00:54:44,730 --> 00:54:46,697
strong and fight this
evil that comes for us?

711
00:54:46,765 --> 00:54:48,266
They are witches.

712
00:54:48,333 --> 00:54:51,135
We have no magic.

713
00:54:51,203 --> 00:54:56,141
What we have is better.

714
00:54:56,208 --> 00:54:59,108
We have our witch hunter.

715
00:54:59,175 --> 00:55:03,212
He showed me that we can
fight magic, and we can win.

716
00:55:03,280 --> 00:55:07,282
Together with his book and our
strength, we will fight the

717
00:55:07,350 --> 00:55:09,017
red queen and we will win.

718
00:55:09,085 --> 00:55:12,353
We will send her and her
army of evil back to hell!

719
00:55:12,420 --> 00:55:14,755
[ All cheering ]

720
00:55:35,175 --> 00:55:38,344
Uhh!

721
00:55:46,287 --> 00:55:49,222
You fight well.

722
00:55:49,290 --> 00:55:51,925
There are few who can match me.

723
00:55:51,993 --> 00:55:54,594
Particularly ones so beautiful.

724
00:55:54,662 --> 00:55:59,132
When she gets what she
wants, she will kill you.

725
00:55:59,200 --> 00:56:02,468
Pretty words can't save you.

726
00:56:02,536 --> 00:56:05,305
She'd have done so already
if she'd intended to.

727
00:56:05,373 --> 00:56:07,674
She intends to trade you for the book.

728
00:56:07,742 --> 00:56:08,541
[ Scoffs ]

729
00:56:08,609 --> 00:56:10,043
It won't work.

730
00:56:10,110 --> 00:56:13,446
My king doesn't bargain with evil.

731
00:56:13,514 --> 00:56:16,583
Then you will die.

732
00:56:16,651 --> 00:56:18,752
I'm already dead.

733
00:56:18,819 --> 00:56:24,156
I gave my word to protect what
is good and what is right.

734
00:56:24,224 --> 00:56:28,293
And I have tried to
do that and failed.

735
00:56:28,361 --> 00:56:33,297
It doesn't matter what
happens to me now.

736
00:56:33,365 --> 00:56:36,400
Foolish.

737
00:56:36,468 --> 00:56:40,170
Is your life so unprecious to
you that you would give it away

738
00:56:40,238 --> 00:56:41,738
so freely for your king?

739
00:56:41,806 --> 00:56:43,606
Because he would die for me.

740
00:56:43,674 --> 00:56:47,677
Is there nothing in your life
important enough to die for?

741
00:56:47,745 --> 00:56:50,346
I'd die for my queen.

742
00:56:50,414 --> 00:56:51,781
Why?

743
00:56:51,849 --> 00:56:54,887
I heard her speaking to you.

744
00:56:54,954 --> 00:56:57,590
You're nothing to her.

745
00:56:57,658 --> 00:57:01,728
She will kill you when
you're no longer useful.

746
00:57:01,796 --> 00:57:04,165
You have to know that.

747
00:57:07,970 --> 00:57:11,106
[ Sighs ]

748
00:57:11,174 --> 00:57:13,944
Think and do what's right.

749
00:57:14,011 --> 00:57:17,414
Let me go back to my kingdom.

750
00:57:17,481 --> 00:57:19,115
[ Chuckles ]

751
00:57:19,183 --> 00:57:23,285
If you help me, I'll help you.

752
00:57:23,353 --> 00:57:26,121
I can promise you that.

753
00:57:35,766 --> 00:57:38,197
You have something?

754
00:57:38,265 --> 00:57:39,397
Here.

755
00:57:39,465 --> 00:57:43,799
This one says "the ones who deal
the fatal blow must look the

756
00:57:43,866 --> 00:57:48,669
ruler in the eyes and repeat
these words... 'not of my

757
00:57:48,736 --> 00:57:51,004
mother, nor my father.

758
00:57:51,072 --> 00:57:53,173
I am borne of light.

759
00:57:53,240 --> 00:57:58,411
My faith, it surrounds me,
protects me from your might.

760
00:57:58,478 --> 00:58:05,584
The earth, the water, the fire,
the sky... in our elemental

761
00:58:05,652 --> 00:58:10,488
"combat, you shall die.'"

762
00:58:10,555 --> 00:58:13,023
[ sighs ]

763
00:58:18,029 --> 00:58:22,932
I fear... I fear I have
no command of sorcery.

764
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:24,867
Think of it like a prayer.

765
00:58:24,934 --> 00:58:28,803
One that might save your
life and your people.

766
00:58:45,819 --> 00:58:51,189
My lord... a strange cloud
approaches from the west.

767
00:58:51,257 --> 00:58:52,857
Gather your men and your weapons.

768
00:58:52,925 --> 00:58:54,459
I'll meet you by the castle's gate.

769
00:58:54,526 --> 00:58:55,826
I have a plan.

770
00:58:55,827 --> 00:59:06,202
His book, and then they
will leave us alone.

771
00:59:06,270 --> 00:59:09,939
And you believe that?

772
00:59:10,007 --> 00:59:12,641
None of this will end until
the red queen is dead.

773
00:59:12,709 --> 00:59:15,944
And you know it.

774
00:59:16,012 --> 00:59:18,713
Ready the archers.

775
00:59:18,781 --> 00:59:19,747
Light the torches.

776
00:59:19,815 --> 00:59:21,682
Ready? Go.

777
00:59:21,750 --> 00:59:25,419
And prepare for battle.

778
01:00:09,523 --> 01:00:11,523
[ All shouting ]

779
01:00:11,591 --> 01:00:18,229
Sire...
You cannot stay here in the open.

780
01:00:18,297 --> 01:00:20,331
Go.

781
01:00:20,399 --> 01:00:21,332
Hide.

782
01:00:21,400 --> 01:00:24,468
And if you die, who
will lead this battle?

783
01:00:24,536 --> 01:00:28,872
Who will restore your kingdom
when the enemy has been defeated?

784
01:00:28,940 --> 01:00:31,908
You have no heir like your father did.

785
01:00:31,976 --> 01:00:34,144
I will fight for my people.

786
01:00:34,212 --> 01:00:37,814
I'm of no use to them
behind locked doors.

787
01:00:37,881 --> 01:00:41,116
Go.

788
01:00:41,184 --> 01:00:47,489
You are a better, wiser man
than your father ever was.

789
01:00:47,557 --> 01:00:51,225
I want to fight by your side.

790
01:00:51,293 --> 01:00:56,730
You are a brave man, madman.

791
01:01:00,635 --> 01:01:03,937
[ Laughs evilly ]

792
01:01:04,004 --> 01:01:08,374
This is what the mighty king
Malachy calls his army?

793
01:01:08,442 --> 01:01:11,510
We will make quick work of you.

794
01:01:14,008 --> 01:01:15,109
Ready your weapons.

795
01:01:28,820 --> 01:01:30,421
The prisoner, my queen.

796
01:01:41,231 --> 01:01:43,231
[ Grunting ]

797
01:01:47,302 --> 01:01:53,273
[ Breathing heavily ]

798
01:01:53,341 --> 01:01:55,775
King Malachy!

799
01:01:55,843 --> 01:01:58,811
Make yourself known.

800
01:01:58,879 --> 01:02:03,448
Deliver me the witch
hunter and that book!

801
01:02:03,515 --> 01:02:06,050
Why should I trust you, witch?

802
01:02:06,118 --> 01:02:09,053
You know we have more power than you.

803
01:02:09,120 --> 01:02:15,793
All I want is the witch
hunter and that book.

804
01:02:15,861 --> 01:02:19,564
In exchange, I'll return your friend.

805
01:02:19,631 --> 01:02:22,533
He's worth something, isn't he?

806
01:02:22,601 --> 01:02:26,003
Do it and it'll be over.

807
01:02:26,071 --> 01:02:28,239
Do you really think that
blackmail would make me betray

808
01:02:28,307 --> 01:02:30,107
my people?

809
01:02:30,175 --> 01:02:34,111
Your witch hunter is a charlatan!

810
01:02:36,815 --> 01:02:38,983
Charlatan?

811
01:02:39,050 --> 01:02:40,284
The north tower. Now.

812
01:02:40,351 --> 01:02:43,053
My witch hunter seems to bother you.

813
01:02:49,694 --> 01:02:51,729
Something's happening.

814
01:03:00,938 --> 01:03:03,773
Let them eat fire!

815
01:03:03,841 --> 01:03:06,609
Now!

816
01:03:06,677 --> 01:03:07,911
Fire!

817
01:03:20,056 --> 01:03:22,223
Get him!

818
01:03:22,291 --> 01:03:23,591
The book.

819
01:03:23,659 --> 01:03:25,326
Our future depends on it.

820
01:03:25,394 --> 01:03:29,263
Make it safe.

821
01:03:29,331 --> 01:03:30,231
You idiot.

822
01:03:30,298 --> 01:03:31,665
Why'd you let him go?

823
01:03:31,733 --> 01:03:34,268
I was trying to protect you, mother.

824
01:03:34,336 --> 01:03:39,007
I'll show you how it's done.

825
01:03:39,075 --> 01:03:42,813
Find the book!

826
01:03:42,881 --> 01:03:45,049
Ready yourselves!

827
01:05:28,304 --> 01:05:30,505
Forgive me, your highness.

828
01:05:30,573 --> 01:05:32,707
You did not help me in life.

829
01:05:32,775 --> 01:05:35,210
Perhaps you will do so in death.

830
01:05:35,277 --> 01:05:36,277
[ Floor creaks ]

831
01:05:42,584 --> 01:05:44,551
[ Grunts ]

832
01:06:03,003 --> 01:06:04,938
What have you done to them?

833
01:06:05,006 --> 01:06:08,108
They're under the red queen's control.

834
01:06:08,175 --> 01:06:13,246
They're her slaves now, so she'll
do what she wants with them.

835
01:06:13,313 --> 01:06:15,414
What will you do?

836
01:06:15,482 --> 01:06:16,916
Kill you.

837
01:06:16,984 --> 01:06:21,120
It's her wish.

838
01:06:21,188 --> 01:06:24,124
You enjoy what little time
you have left, pretty boy.

839
01:06:24,192 --> 01:06:25,259
[ Spits ]

840
01:06:31,333 --> 01:06:33,869
[ Grunting ]

841
01:06:42,279 --> 01:06:44,748
King Malachy.

842
01:06:44,816 --> 01:06:50,054
Please...
Don't embarrass yourself anymore.

843
01:06:50,122 --> 01:06:53,424
You are still king...
For the moment.

844
01:06:53,492 --> 01:06:55,793
Why didn't you kill me?

845
01:06:55,861 --> 01:06:57,094
Kill you?

846
01:06:57,162 --> 01:06:59,330
You have the kingdom.

847
01:06:59,398 --> 01:07:01,298
[ Scoffs ]

848
01:07:01,366 --> 01:07:09,707
Why would I destroy the one thing
I have wanted all these years?

849
01:07:09,774 --> 01:07:16,013
Next to escape from that dismal village,
I have waited only for you.

850
01:07:16,081 --> 01:07:18,215
Me?

851
01:07:18,283 --> 01:07:20,184
Why me?

852
01:07:20,252 --> 01:07:27,192
Because you, Malachy, you're my son.

853
01:07:27,259 --> 01:07:28,893
[ Breathing heavily ]

854
01:07:28,961 --> 01:07:32,096
[ Laughs ]

855
01:07:35,199 --> 01:07:38,567
You're my son, Malachy.

856
01:07:38,634 --> 01:07:43,270
My father told me my mother was dead.

857
01:07:43,338 --> 01:07:44,705
Indeed.

858
01:07:44,773 --> 01:07:51,643
A small part of me died giving
birth to you and your sister.

859
01:07:51,711 --> 01:07:53,611
Look. Look.

860
01:07:53,679 --> 01:07:55,414
No!

861
01:07:55,482 --> 01:07:57,984
Your father was desperate for an heir.

862
01:07:58,052 --> 01:08:01,617
When your sister was born, he
was disappointed, but it didn't

863
01:08:01,685 --> 01:08:02,949
trouble him for long.

864
01:08:03,017 --> 01:08:05,615
You arrived only minutes
after your sister.

865
01:08:05,683 --> 01:08:07,518
Your father had his heir.

866
01:08:07,585 --> 01:08:11,286
That night, you became ill
and were taken from us.

867
01:08:11,354 --> 01:08:18,059
I did what any mother would do if she had
the power, but he was afraid of my magic.

868
01:08:18,127 --> 01:08:20,328
He banished me.

869
01:08:20,395 --> 01:08:28,168
I begged him... begged him... to
let me take you and your sister.

870
01:08:28,236 --> 01:08:34,040
He allowed me to take my
daughter, but not his son.

871
01:08:34,108 --> 01:08:36,408
"I curse you and your kingdom."

872
01:08:36,476 --> 01:08:40,579
I have saved your son, and
this is how you thank me?

873
01:08:40,647 --> 01:08:45,283
"You will regret this betrayal
until your dying day."

874
01:08:45,351 --> 01:08:47,919
He lied to me.

875
01:08:47,987 --> 01:08:51,856
He told you I died in
childbirth, didn't he?

876
01:08:51,924 --> 01:08:52,690
Yes.

877
01:08:52,758 --> 01:08:55,893
Oh, you are my son.

878
01:08:55,961 --> 01:08:58,929
Otherwise, I would have killed you.

879
01:08:58,997 --> 01:09:02,398
What do you want from this?

880
01:09:02,466 --> 01:09:07,970
I was given a powerful gift ... the same
gift that you were born with.

881
01:09:08,037 --> 01:09:14,042
There is no stronger bond than
that of mother and child.

882
01:09:14,109 --> 01:09:19,513
Don't you feel the... the blood
running through your veins?

883
01:09:19,580 --> 01:09:24,751
Oh, accept your parentage.

884
01:09:24,818 --> 01:09:29,989
Together, we can reign in the triumvirate
of mind, body, and soul.

885
01:09:30,056 --> 01:09:32,057
And sister is sword?

886
01:09:32,125 --> 01:09:33,525
Yes. Jozefa.

887
01:09:33,592 --> 01:09:37,728
She has the gift of dark
magic, just as you do.

888
01:09:37,796 --> 01:09:43,000
We will be stronger than any
other ruler in the world.

889
01:09:43,068 --> 01:09:45,235
Huh?

890
01:09:45,303 --> 01:09:46,970
Never.

891
01:09:47,038 --> 01:09:49,239
[ Scoffs ]

892
01:09:49,306 --> 01:09:50,773
Look into my eyes.

893
01:09:50,841 --> 01:09:53,175
See the truth.

894
01:09:53,243 --> 01:09:57,112
I'm not going to hurt you.

895
01:09:57,179 --> 01:10:00,948
Oh, don't be afraid.

896
01:10:01,016 --> 01:10:05,518
It is not fear I feel for you.

897
01:10:13,426 --> 01:10:16,127
[ Breathing heavily ]

898
01:10:16,195 --> 01:10:23,298
Tell us where the book is, fiend.

899
01:10:23,366 --> 01:10:24,599
Never.

900
01:10:31,771 --> 01:10:35,773
Maybe you'd like to be
more comfortable, then.

901
01:10:35,841 --> 01:10:37,240
[ Breathing heavily ]

902
01:11:13,140 --> 01:11:14,874
No!

903
01:11:14,942 --> 01:11:15,975
Nooooo!

904
01:11:17,040 --> 01:11:18,675
What is it?

905
01:11:26,653 --> 01:11:31,423
Your witch hunter has more
spirit than he displays.

906
01:11:31,491 --> 01:11:36,527
Once more... where is that book?

907
01:11:36,595 --> 01:11:41,566
Why do you reject this
power I'm offering you?

908
01:11:41,634 --> 01:11:43,234
Why?

909
01:11:47,573 --> 01:11:51,576
Because I am my people's king.

910
01:11:51,643 --> 01:11:53,811
And I will die for them
before I tell you.

911
01:11:53,879 --> 01:11:57,281
The people of your kingdom
will be my slaves.

912
01:11:57,348 --> 01:12:02,953
I will rule them as I see
fit until you join me.

913
01:12:03,021 --> 01:12:06,356
This is your doing.

914
01:12:06,424 --> 01:12:08,125
Take him to the dungeon.

915
01:12:08,192 --> 01:12:11,195
[ Grunts ]

916
01:12:16,202 --> 01:12:21,270
You have a choice.

917
01:12:21,338 --> 01:12:26,039
Or is killing me gonna help
you please your queen?

918
01:12:26,107 --> 01:12:28,341
And then what?

919
01:12:28,408 --> 01:12:31,043
Who else will you have
to murder for her?

920
01:12:31,111 --> 01:12:34,513
Silence.

921
01:12:34,581 --> 01:12:43,788
You're her executioner,
and nothing else.

922
01:12:43,856 --> 01:12:46,224
[ Sniffles ]

923
01:12:46,291 --> 01:12:57,134
And the king, your friend...
Is my brother.

924
01:12:57,202 --> 01:13:02,371
But you, you are nothing.

925
01:13:02,439 --> 01:13:08,909
If you will not give us the book,
then there is no use for you.

926
01:13:08,977 --> 01:13:15,153
And what happens when you
are no longer useful?

927
01:13:15,221 --> 01:13:16,821
Leave us!

928
01:13:25,663 --> 01:13:28,030
Jozefa.

929
01:13:28,098 --> 01:13:31,132
Jozefa!

930
01:13:31,200 --> 01:13:32,667
I know there's good in you!

931
01:13:32,734 --> 01:13:34,735
I can see it in you!

932
01:13:39,473 --> 01:13:41,074
Jozefa!

933
01:13:41,141 --> 01:13:43,275
[ Grunting ]

934
01:14:02,292 --> 01:14:04,492
[ Breathing heavily ]

935
01:14:14,100 --> 01:14:16,201
I have failed you, my friend.

936
01:14:16,268 --> 01:14:17,769
No.

937
01:14:17,836 --> 01:14:20,637
We must keep the book safe.

938
01:14:20,704 --> 01:14:26,407
If we give up our knowledge of the black
arts, we will doom all humanity.

939
01:14:26,474 --> 01:14:27,841
No. No.

940
01:14:27,909 --> 01:14:32,377
Remember where you came from.

941
01:14:32,445 --> 01:14:36,281
It's there you'll find what you seek.

942
01:14:36,349 --> 01:14:41,286
I come from the devil.

943
01:14:41,354 --> 01:14:47,892
The red queen...
I am her son.

944
01:14:47,959 --> 01:14:51,963
My father banished her.

945
01:14:52,031 --> 01:14:57,237
He kept the dark truth
from all of us for years.

946
01:14:57,305 --> 01:14:59,741
Her son?

947
01:14:59,808 --> 01:15:02,644
Do you know what this means?

948
01:15:02,712 --> 01:15:05,981
Yes. That I am cursed.

949
01:15:06,049 --> 01:15:10,352
No. You are blessed.

950
01:15:10,420 --> 01:15:14,623
Remember what the book said.

951
01:15:14,691 --> 01:15:21,196
"Death will come if the essence
she once shared in love..."

952
01:15:21,264 --> 01:15:24,800
"It will return in full
with grace and sacrifice."

953
01:15:24,868 --> 01:15:25,968
Yes, of course.

954
01:15:26,036 --> 01:15:27,837
That's it.

955
01:15:27,904 --> 01:15:34,076
Her blood, her essence,
flows through your veins.

956
01:15:34,144 --> 01:15:40,149
You...You are the one.

957
01:15:40,216 --> 01:15:44,286
Only you can kill her.

958
01:16:07,343 --> 01:16:09,010
Jozefa!

959
01:16:09,078 --> 01:16:10,879
Please!

960
01:16:10,946 --> 01:16:12,446
Please, Jozefa!

961
01:16:33,069 --> 01:16:38,307
I must ask, mother, when were you
going to share the good news

962
01:16:38,374 --> 01:16:39,808
that I had a brother?

963
01:16:39,876 --> 01:16:42,244
Is that all that troubles you?

964
01:16:42,311 --> 01:16:45,213
I thought you were going to moan
about having to get rid of that

965
01:16:45,281 --> 01:16:47,616
rather handsome young man.

966
01:16:55,391 --> 01:16:58,960
No, it would have been nice
to know that I had a brother.

967
01:16:59,028 --> 01:17:00,361
Someone to protect me.

968
01:17:00,429 --> 01:17:02,297
Someone to share secrets with.

969
01:17:02,364 --> 01:17:05,433
You know all about secrets,
don't you, my queen?

970
01:17:05,501 --> 01:17:08,102
You grow tiresome, my child.

971
01:17:08,170 --> 01:17:10,405
Why are you doing this?

972
01:17:10,472 --> 01:17:13,841
I have waited years for
your brother to return.

973
01:17:13,909 --> 01:17:19,046
Now the day has come when all that was
taken from me is about to be restored.

974
01:17:19,114 --> 01:17:23,984
My triumvirate is only complete
when all three of us are together.

975
01:17:24,052 --> 01:17:26,019
What?

976
01:17:26,087 --> 01:17:30,057
Are we all to sit side-by-side
doing your evil bidding?

977
01:17:30,124 --> 01:17:31,024
Enough.

978
01:17:31,092 --> 01:17:32,059
Or what?

979
01:17:32,126 --> 01:17:34,260
Will you have me killed, too?

980
01:17:34,328 --> 01:17:37,296
What will that do to your plans?

981
01:17:55,983 --> 01:18:03,759
Do you want to just take
that down for a moment?

982
01:18:03,826 --> 01:18:05,360
I'm not a murderer.

983
01:18:05,428 --> 01:18:13,434
You and I must kill the red
queen, whatever the cost.

984
01:18:13,502 --> 01:18:18,439
Do you know where the
king's being held?

985
01:18:18,507 --> 01:18:20,374
I'll take you there.

986
01:18:41,730 --> 01:18:45,600
I will... I will kill you
for what you did to him!

987
01:18:45,667 --> 01:18:48,737
I will kill you for
what you did to him!

988
01:18:48,804 --> 01:18:50,272
Calm yourself!

989
01:18:50,340 --> 01:18:52,641
Calm yourself. Calm yourself.

990
01:18:52,709 --> 01:18:55,111
Calm yourself.

991
01:18:55,178 --> 01:18:57,613
Not at her. Listen to me.

992
01:18:57,681 --> 01:19:00,050
She's with us now, okay?

993
01:19:00,117 --> 01:19:01,751
You're alive. You're alive.

994
01:19:01,819 --> 01:19:02,853
We have to go.

995
01:19:02,920 --> 01:19:03,920
We have to hurry.

996
01:19:03,988 --> 01:19:04,988
We have to hurry.

997
01:19:05,056 --> 01:19:07,425
Release him!

998
01:19:26,209 --> 01:19:28,243
He was a great man.

999
01:19:59,737 --> 01:20:01,971
[ Gasps ]

1000
01:20:02,039 --> 01:20:03,973
[ Sighs ]

1001
01:20:15,853 --> 01:20:19,021
My wait is over.

1002
01:20:22,493 --> 01:20:24,727
The time has come.

1003
01:20:24,795 --> 01:20:25,828
Make ready.

1004
01:20:38,973 --> 01:20:42,142
Show her no fear.

1005
01:20:42,210 --> 01:20:45,578
And show her no mercy.

1006
01:21:01,796 --> 01:21:05,298
How dare you interrupt the ceremony.

1007
01:21:05,366 --> 01:21:06,700
But no matter.

1008
01:21:06,767 --> 01:21:09,669
At last, my power will be complete.

1009
01:21:09,737 --> 01:21:13,706
It is not power we bring, mother.

1010
01:21:13,774 --> 01:21:16,075
It is death.

1011
01:21:16,143 --> 01:21:19,278
Children.

1012
01:21:19,346 --> 01:21:23,282
Do you not feel the energy
of the triumvirate?

1013
01:21:23,350 --> 01:21:25,518
We are together, stronger.

1014
01:21:25,585 --> 01:21:28,053
We will rule the world as one.

1015
01:21:28,121 --> 01:21:30,255
It ends here.

1016
01:21:30,323 --> 01:21:32,025
Now.

1017
01:21:32,093 --> 01:21:33,994
The light races through our veins.

1018
01:21:34,062 --> 01:21:36,864
We are here to kill you.

1019
01:21:36,932 --> 01:21:40,301
My will.

1020
01:21:40,369 --> 01:21:41,669
Jozefa!

1021
01:21:41,737 --> 01:21:43,404
Do not doubt our conviction, mother.

1022
01:21:43,472 --> 01:21:44,472
You are no match for us.

1023
01:21:53,576 --> 01:21:56,612
Your power is no match for mine.

1024
01:21:56,679 --> 01:22:02,916
I have taught you too much,
perhaps, but not everything.

1025
01:22:02,984 --> 01:22:04,217
Jozefa!

1026
01:22:14,693 --> 01:22:15,860
Jason!

1027
01:22:15,928 --> 01:22:16,862
What have you done to him?

1028
01:22:20,567 --> 01:22:22,168
Aaaaaah!

1029
01:22:26,540 --> 01:22:27,373
Aaaaah!

1030
01:22:44,422 --> 01:22:45,889
Jason!

1031
01:23:01,704 --> 01:23:04,873
Jason! Remember who you are!

1032
01:23:04,941 --> 01:23:06,341
She's not with us.

1033
01:23:06,409 --> 01:23:07,642
I am your king!

1034
01:23:07,710 --> 01:23:08,977
Are you with me?

1035
01:23:09,045 --> 01:23:11,247
I'm with you, my lord.

1036
01:23:48,953 --> 01:23:50,554
Mother.

1037
01:23:50,621 --> 01:23:53,190
I cannot, and I will not, allow
you to destroy my kingdom.

1038
01:23:53,258 --> 01:23:56,425
You're my son.

1039
01:23:56,493 --> 01:23:58,493
Malachy, we must do it.

1040
01:24:13,142 --> 01:24:14,977
[ Woman vocalizing ]

1041
01:24:23,486 --> 01:24:29,057
"Death will come to the one who
rules the fiery coven only"

1042
01:24:29,125 --> 01:24:35,095
if the essence that she once
shared in love returns to her in

1043
01:24:35,162 --> 01:24:38,264
"full with grace and sacrifice."

1044
01:24:59,553 --> 01:25:06,158
Not of my mother, nor my father.

1045
01:25:06,226 --> 01:25:08,594
I am borne of light.

1046
01:25:08,662 --> 01:25:12,097
My faith, it surrounds me.

1047
01:25:12,165 --> 01:25:14,333
It protects me from your might.

1048
01:25:14,401 --> 01:25:22,573
The earth, water, the fire, and
sky... in our elemental combat,

1049
01:25:22,641 --> 01:25:23,974
you shall die.

1050
01:25:24,042 --> 01:25:26,076
[ Grunts, gasps ]

1051
01:25:32,383 --> 01:25:33,883
Aaah!

1052
01:26:01,015 --> 01:26:04,584
We are victorious against
the army of evil.

1053
01:26:04,652 --> 01:26:08,321
But our victory has
come at a great price.

1054
01:26:08,389 --> 01:26:16,329
Today we honor a warrior, a
brother, and a dear friend.

1055
01:26:16,397 --> 01:26:20,666
A friend whose loyalty to the
kingdom, to my father, and to me

1056
01:26:20,733 --> 01:26:25,070
will keep his memory strong
for people and king to come.

1057
01:26:25,138 --> 01:26:27,939
Today we enjoy our freedom.

1058
01:26:28,007 --> 01:26:29,408
We live with hope.

1059
01:26:29,475 --> 01:26:37,050
We must let his sacrifice remind us always
that together we are strong.

1060
01:26:37,118 --> 01:26:43,490
Together...
We are Dragonoff.

